article.headline: Temple 83, Duquesne 65
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- David Hawkins scored 27 points and Mardy Collins had a career-high 26 to lead Temple to its fifth straight victory, an 83-65 win over Duquesne Wednesday night. Freshman Tyreek Byard tied a career-high with 10 points for the Owls (12-10, 6-5 Atlantic 10). Dustin Salisbery also had 10. Bryant McAllister scored 13 points to lead the Dukes (9-14, 4-8), who have lost six of seven. Kieron Achara and Elijah Palmer both added 12. Hawkins had five steals, equaled his season-high with five 3-pointers and scored more than 20 for an NCAA-leading 17th straight game. Collins made nine of his first 11 field-goal attempts and finished 11-for-17. The Owls -- last in the conference in field goal percentage -- were uncharacteristically accurate in the first half, hitting 16 of 29 attempts. Collins hit a pair of turnaround jumpers and Salisbery hit two 3s during a 10-0 run that closed the first half and gave Temple a 42-29 lead. Hawkins, Collins and Byard each made a 3 in the opening 3:11 of the second half to help push the lead to 19. Hawkins and Collins combined for 21 points the rest of the way, as the Dukes got no closer than 13 down the stretch. The Owls had a season-low four turnovers.
